<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="74" type="distribution">
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6635168" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6635168" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6635168/files/figure.png" inLine="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="74" targetBox="[1370,1950,1997,2402]" targetPageId="8">
<paragraph blockId="8.[1982,2567,1990,2411]" pageId="8" pageNumber="74">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1982,2158,2182,2215]" pageId="8" pageNumber="74">Distribution.</emphasis>
SW Madagascar, known only from the Zombitse-Vohibasia National Park region, N of the Onilahy River and S of the Fiherena River. Additional surveys are needed to determine the N, W, and E boundaries of the distribution.
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="74" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="8.[1362,2568,2416,3195]" pageId="8" pageNumber="74">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1366,1615,2416,2449]" pageId="8" pageNumber="74">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head-body 23-24 cm, tail ¢.24 cm; weight 990 g. A medium-sized to large species ofsportive lemur. The dorsal pelage is dark reddish-brown around the shoulders and upper back, gradually becoming a lighter reddish-white to gray toward the base of the tail and hips. The underside is entirely white, and the tail is uniformly blonde or reddish-blonde. The face is grayish-brown around the muzzle and eyes, with a reddish-brown dorsal surface crown, and the fur around the neck is lighter, forming a reddish-blonde collar. Two phenotypes have been observed, possibly the male and the female butthis has yet to be confirmed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[1364,1630,2732,2761]" pageId="8" pageNumber="74" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="8.[1362,2568,2416,3195]" box="[1364,1630,2732,2761]" pageId="8" pageNumber="74">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1364,1475,2732,2761]" pageId="8" pageNumber="74">Habitat.</emphasis>
Dry forest.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="74" type="food_feeding">
<paragraph blockId="8.[1362,2568,2416,3195]" pageId="8" pageNumber="74">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1364,1626,2770,2803]" pageId="8" pageNumber="74">Food and Feeding.</emphasis>
There is no specific information available for this species, butitis presumably largely folivorous.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[1364,2198,2847,2880]" pageId="8" pageNumber="74" type="breeding">
