</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="74" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="8.[1362,2568,2416,3195]" pageId="8" pageNumber="74">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1363,1711,3005,3038]" pageId="8" pageNumber="74">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
CITES Appendix I. Classified as Data Deficient on The IUCN Red List. However, at the IUCN/SSC Lemur Red-Listing Workshop held in July 2012, 
<taxonomicName box="[1364,1514,3088,3117]" class="Mammalia" family="Lepilemuridae" genus="Lepilemur" kingdom="Animalia" order="Primates" pageId="8" pageNumber="74" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hubbardi">L. hubbardi</taxonomicName>
was assessed as endangered. The only protected area in which this species is known to occur is the Zombitse-Vohibasia National Park.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
